# Public assets directory

Place your images, fonts, and other static files here.

## Recommended Structure

```
public/
├── images/
│   ├── profile.jpg          # Your profile photo
│   └── projects/            # Project screenshots
├── favicon-16x16.png        # Small favicon
├── favicon-32x32.png        # Medium favicon
├── apple-touch-icon.png     # Apple touch icon (180x180)
└── resume.pdf               # Your resume
```

## Creating Favicons (Optional)

You can use tools like:
- [Favicon.io](https://favicon.io) - Generate from text/image
- [RealFaviconGenerator](https://realfavicongenerator.net) - Complete favicon package

Or just use emoji as favicon temporarily:
1. Go to https://favicon.io/emoji-favicons/
2. Download your favorite emoji favicon
3. Extract and place PNG files in `/public`

## Image Optimization

Next.js automatically optimizes images when using the `next/image` component:

- Automatic WebP conversion
- Responsive images
- Lazy loading
- Blur placeholder

## Adding New Assets

1. Place files in appropriate subdirectory
2. Reference them in components:
   ```tsx
   import Image from 'next/image'
   
   <Image src="/images/profile.jpg" alt="..." width={400} height={400} />
   ```

3. For non-image files (PDFs, etc.):
   ```tsx
   <a href="/resume.pdf" download>Download Resume</a>
   ```

## Note

The favicon configuration is in `app/layout.tsx`. If you don't add favicon files,
the browser will use its default icon (which is fine for development).

